==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peag
<hw>Peag</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧g)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>peage</asp>, <asp>peak</asp>, <asp>peeke</asp>.]</altsp>
<ety>[Prob. of North American Indian origin, by shortening of
<ets>wampumpeag</ets>. <au>RHUD</au>.]</ety> <def>A kind of aboriginal
shell money, or wampum, of the Atlantic coast of the United States; --
originally applied only to polished white cylindrical beads. See also
<er>wampum</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peage</ent>⟦br⟧
